<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E74C53BFF3FBFCCFCADEC77" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E74C53BFF3FBFCCFCADEC77" blockId="118.[151,1436,151,463]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFF3FBFCCFE97ED93" bold="true" box="[199,321,223,248]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
6.0 mm long; pronotum and MP dingy yellow, MS dark brown; deflexed elytral apex rounded; distinguished by the bilobed PLP (
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E74C53BFDE1BE17FD09EC77" author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[537,735,260,284]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" pagination="117 - 170" refId="ref122195" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 a) Further Revisional Studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 113, 117 - 170." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne 1987a</bibRefCitation>
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E74C53BFD1EBE17FCBBEC77" box="[742,877,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–5" captionStartId="10.[151,263,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[290,1309,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-108@10.[282,1309,173,1922]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 3–5. Majority rule tree for the complete analysis of the Luciolinae. Analysis consisted of consensus of 169 MPTs with a length of 5609 from a data set of 143 taxa and 436 morphological characters in (see Table 3). Figure 3, part 1: nodes 1– 34; 4, part 2 Nodes 35–52; 5, part 3 nodes 55–76. Nodes (red). New genera, new species, and still undescribed species in red and bold, with identification numbers blue. Black values above branches show the % of MPTs over 50 %." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265348/files/figure.png" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5a, b, c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E74C53BFF3FBE3BFEDCECA4" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E74C53BFF3FBE3BFEDCECA4" blockId="118.[151,1436,151,463]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFF3FBE3BFEEDEC2B" bold="true" box="[199,315,296,320]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E74C53BFEBCBE34FE30EC54" author="Olivier, E." box="[324,486,295,319]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" pagination="333 - 374" refId="ref128538" refString="Olivier, E. (1885) Catalogue des Lampyrides faisant partie des collections du Musee Civique de Genes. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, (2 a) 2, 333 - 374." type="journal article" year="1885">Olivier (1885)</bibRefCitation>
named the species for the small size of its pronotum, and 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E74C53BFB72BE34FF37EC0F" author="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; McLean, M. R." pageId="118" pageNumber="119" pagination="223 - 305" refId="ref122809" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; McLean, M. R. (1970) Revisional studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae: Luciolini). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 96, 223 - 305." type="journal article" year="1970">Ballantyne and McLean (1970)</bibRefCitation>
adopted an E/P index (ratio of elytral width measured across bases to pronotal width) in an attempt to characterise it. The use of this index has been discontinued; 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E74C53BFCBEBE63FC19ECE3" authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1885" box="[838,975,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microthorax">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFCBEBE63FC19ECE3" box="[838,975,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">microthorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is amply characterised by features of its terminal abdomen. 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E74C53BFE80BE87FDB3ECC7" author="Helgen, K. &amp; Leary, T. &amp; Doria G. &amp; Amori, G." box="[376,613,404,428]" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" pagination="653 - 686" refId="ref126041" refString="Helgen, K. M, Leary, T., Doria G., &amp; Amori, G. (2008) Catalogue of Melanesian rodents in the Museum of Genova (Mammalia: Rodentia). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia naturale G. Doria, 99, 653 - 686." type="journal article" year="2008">
Helgen 
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E74C53BFE2CBE86FDC6ECC7" box="[468,528,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated Hatam is a village in the Arfak Mountains of the Vogelkop peninsula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
